{"uid":"866922eab315ba31","name":"[BUG-SF-006] TC-SF-012 — GET /api/v1/fetch/trigger: Must return 405 Method Not Allowed (returns 500)","fullName":"oauth-token-spr-fetcher-api.spec.ts:1272:7","historyId":"b2235da525dd6b14ad142ddad09a4233:4ff26534acff1e0ca6b9eaf99e336bac","time":{"start":1783299345607,"stop":1783299346265,"duration":658},"description":"**[KNOWN BUG — BUG-SF-006]**\n\n**What this test does:**\nSends a GET request to /api/v1/fetch/trigger (a POST-only endpoint) and verifies the server returns 405 Method Not Allowed.\n\n**Expected:** HTTP 405 Method Not Allowed with Allow: POST header\n**Actual:** HTTP 500 Internal Server Error\n\n**Root Cause:** Same as BUG-SF-005 — unhandled MethodNotAllowedException produces 500.\n\n**Common scenario where this occurs:** A developer calls GET /fetch/trigger expecting to see the trigger status or last-run time. Instead they get a confusing 500 with no indication that they used the wrong HTTP method.","descriptionHtml":"<p><strong>[KNOWN BUG — BUG-SF-006]</strong></p>\n<p><strong>What this test does:</strong><br />\nSends a GET request to /api/v1/fetch/trigger (a POST-only endpoint) and verifies the server returns 405 Method Not Allowed.</p>\n<p><strong>Expected:</strong> HTTP 405 Method Not Allowed with Allow: POST header<br />\n<strong>Actual:</strong> HTTP 500 Internal Server Error</p>\n<p><strong>Root Cause:</strong> Same as BUG-SF-005 — unhandled MethodNotAllowedException produces 500.</p>\n<p><strong>Common scenario where this occurs:</strong> A developer calls GET /fetch/trigger expecting to see the trigger status or last-run time. Instead they get a confusing 500 with no indication that they used the wrong HTTP method.</p>\n","status":"passed","flaky":false,"newFailed":false,"newBroken":false,"newPassed":false,"retriesCount":0,"retriesStatusChange":false,"beforeStages":[],"testStage":{"description":"**[KNOWN BUG — BUG-SF-006]**\n\n**What this test does:**\nSends a GET request to /api/v1/fetch/trigger (a POST-on